### Critical UI Components:
1. **Grove Explorer**: Visual tree of projects, branches, and vessels
2. **Agent Collaboration Panel**: Real-time agent status and communication
3. **Quality Gate Dashboard**: Guardian review status and approvals
4. **Knowledge Tree Viewer**: Persistent project state and learning
5. **Tool Registry Interface**: Dynamic tool management and permissions

## ðŸš€ Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: Core IDE Foundation (Weeks 1-2)
- Basic grove/branch/vessel management interface
- File system integration and project loading
- User authentication and multi-tenant support
- Basic code editor with syntax highlighting

### Phase 2: DRYAD Integration (Weeks 3-4)
- DRYAD ecosystem service integration
- Knowledge tree persistence and retrieval
- Tool Registry connection and validation
- Basic agent communication framework

### Phase 3: GAD Agent System (Weeks 5-6)
- 4-layer GAD agent integration (Forest Keeper, Guardian, Branch Weaver, Human Provost)
- Agent orchestration interface
- Quality gate workflow implementation
- Real-time agent collaboration features

### Phase 4: Advanced Features (Weeks 7-8)
- Advanced code editing with agent assistance
- Oracle consultation interface
- University curriculum integration
- Performance optimization and testing

## âœ… Success Criteria

### Functional Requirements:
- [ ] Create and manage development groves (projects)
- [ ] Visual branch management with GAD agent integration
- [ ] Vessel storage for deliverables with knowledge persistence
- [ ] Real-time agent collaboration and communication
- [ ] Quality gate enforcement through Guardian reviews
- [ ] DRYAD ecosystem integration (University, Tool Registry, Knowledge Trees)
- [ ] Multi-tenant client isolation and security

### Technical Requirements:
- [ ] Web-based IDE with modern responsive UI
- [ ] Real-time WebSocket communication for agents
- [ ] RESTful API for all CRUD operations
- [ ] Docker containerization for development environment
- [ ] Comprehensive test coverage (>90%)
- [ ] Performance optimization for concurrent users
- [ ] Security compliance with DRYAD standards

### Integration Requirements:
- [ ] ROO-Forge GAD mode integration
- [ ] DRYAD University System curriculum access
- [ ] Tool Registry dynamic tool management
- [ ] Knowledge Tree persistent storage
- [ ] Multi-agent dialogue system connectivity

## ðŸ”§ Development Commands & Setup

### Initial Setup:
```bash
# Clone and setup
git clone <repository>
cd dryad-grove-ide
pip install -r requirements.txt
npm install

# Database setup
alembic upgrade head
python scripts/seed_dryad_data.py

# Start development
npm run dev  # Frontend
uvicorn main:app --reload  # Backend
```

### Testing Commands:
```bash
# Run tests
pytest tests/ --cov=backend --cov-report=html
npm run test

# Integration testing
pytest tests/integration/test_dryad_integration.py
```

